Business Briefs
Hewlett-Packard Co., a maker of computers and measurement
equipment, got a $37.5 million contract spanning more than
five years to provide a world-wide computing network for
Australia's Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade.
   ---
   Domtar Inc. will permanently shut the newsprint machine
and reorganize lineboard operations at its Red Rock, Ontario,
mill in May. The measures will cut the facility's 600-person
work force in half.
   ---
   Marriott Corp. said it completed the sale of 13 hotels to
affiliates of W.P. Carey Co. and Trammell Co. for $146
million. Proceeds will be used to reduce debt.
   ---
   Eastman Kodak Co. said it signed a joint agreement to sell
and distribute the Fiery ColorLaser controller from
Electronics for Imaging Corp., San Bruno, Calif. Kodak will
begin selling the controller, which has a list price of
$35,000, in the U.S. and Canada this year.